      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">The need</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-5">María needed invitations that worked in two worlds: the elegance of something physical and beautiful to hand-deliver, and the convenience of digital for guests who live far away or prefer to confirm online.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">She also wanted to eliminate RSVP confusion — no missed calls, no unanswered messages. She needed to know exactly who confirmed and when.</p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">What we did</h2>
      <ul class="checklist mb-8">
        <li><strong>Physical invitation design</strong> — custom design for María's wedding: elegant typography, coordinated color palette, event details presented clearly and beautifully.</li>
        <li><strong>QR code for RSVP confirmation</strong> — each physical invitation includes a QR code that takes the guest directly to a confirmation form. Simple, fast, no phone call required.</li>
        <li><strong>Animated digital invitations</strong> — animated digital version of the invitation, ready to share on WhatsApp, email, or social media. The same elegance as the physical design, with motion.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">The result</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-6">Guests received something that genuinely looked special — both on paper and on screen. The QR code simplified the confirmation process, and the animated version generated positive comments before the wedding day even arrived.</p>

